dependencies on Debian GNU/Linux 7.2 (wheezy)

* libv4l-dev libfltk1.1-dev

suggested:
* v4l-utils for v4l2-ctl and v4l-utils-1.0.0.tar.bz2

Query devices:
$ v4l2-ctl --all

Query controls:
$ v4l2-ctl -d /dev/video0 -L

Set controls (for example exposure)
$ v4l2-ctl --set-ctrl=exposure_absolute=100

Live Image:
$ mplayer tv:// -tv driver=v4l2:device=/dev/video0

Capture Video:
$ ffmpeg -f v4l2 -r 25 -s 640x480 -i /dev/video0 out.avi

Loopback
$ sudo modprobe v4l2loopback
$ gst-launch-0.10 videotestsrc ! v4l2sink device=/dev/video0

